HEADWORD: Strangury
<hw>Stran"gu*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stranguria</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/, <?/, a drop + <?/ to make water,
<?/ urine: cf. F. <ets>strangurie</ets>. See <er>Strangle</er>, and
<er>Urine</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A painful
discharge of urine, drop by drop, produced by spasmodic muscular
contraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A swelling or other disease in a
plant, occasioned by a ligature fastened tightly about it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strany</ent>⟦br⟧
